When looking at the segments of the baby cribs market, product type plays a critical role in defining consumer choices. Standard baby cribs have been a popular choice for many years due to their versatility and durability. Convertible baby cribs are gaining traction among consumers who value long-term use and versatility in furniture. Portable and travel baby cribs cater to the need for mobility and convenience. Distribution channels also shape the market, with online retail expanding rapidly due to the ease of comparing products and convenient delivery options. Offline retail remains significant, particularly for consumers who prefer to see products in person before making a purchase. Material choice is another important segment, with wood being a traditional favorite for its sturdiness and aesthetic appeal, while metal and plastic offer different advantages in terms of weight and ease of cleaning.

